%N A391598 Primes that are perimeter^2 + hypotenuse^2 of a Pythagorean triple.
%C A391598 Primes of the form (2*x^2 + 2*x*y)^2 + (x^2+y^2)^2 where 0 < y < x.
%C A391598 Are there any such primes that occur for more than one (x,y) pair?
%H A391598 Robert Israel, <a href="/A391598/b391598.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%e A391598 a(3) = 3761 is a term because with x = 4, y = 3 the Pythagorean triple (x^2-y^2 = 7, 2*x*y = 24, x^2 + y^2 = 25) has perimeter 7 + 24 + 25 = 56 and 56^2 + 25^2 = 3761 which is prime.
%p A391598 N:= 10^7: R:= NULL: count:= 0:
%p A391598 for x from 1 while 5*x^4 < N do
%p A391598   for y from 1 to x-1 do
%p A391598     q:= (x^2+y^2)^2 + (2*x*(x+y))^2;
%p A391598     if q > N then break fi;
%p A391598     if igcd(x,y) > 1 then next fi;
%p A391598     if isprime(q) then count:= count+1; R:= R,q fi
%p A391598 od od:
%p A391598 sort([R]);
